    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "ABOUT FLORA\n\nWe build creative tools for the new creative class—an intelligent canvas where the best AI models enable professional craft. We're a team of ~20, with $52M of capital raised from exceptional investors like Redpoint Ventures, Hanabi Capital, Menlo Ventures, Justin Kan, and Gabe Whaley (founder of MSCHF). Our customers span a variety of creative industries and include Pentagram, Lionsgate, and Nike.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nWe're looking to bring on our first growth engineer.\n\nIn this role, you'll design and ship experiments to drive user acquisition, activation, and retention, working closely with product \u0026 design to build data-informed features that move our key metrics while working with our visual language and brand identity.\n\nRequirements\n\n - Obsessed with creative tools - is proficient in at least three creative tools or has built one before\n\n - Extensive experience in quick iteration and A/B testing fo growth strategies and features.\n\n - Familiar with Posthog or similar quantitative user tracking tools.\n\n - Comfortable with all parts of the stack — you have no trouble context-switching from editing CSS to tuning database queries.\n\n - Solid experience with React, JavaScript/Typescript, HTML, CSS and modern front-end build systems (Webpack, ES6, etc).\n\n - Ideally familiar with production JavaScript / Node backends.\n\n - 5+ years experience\n\nStack\n\nWe’re a React + Next.js + TypeScript app with a real-time collaboration layer.\nOur graphics foundation is built on WebGL, Three.js, and React Three Fiber, with backend infrastructure powered by Vercel, Convex and Modal.",
